  "texts": [
    "Introduction and ObjectiveOver the last few years artificial intelligence/machine learning (AI/ML) has been increasingly used throughout drug development and across therapeutic areas from drug discovery, non-clinical and clinical research, clinical trial management, and drug manufacturing to post marketing safety surveillance [1][2][3][4][5][6][7][8].",
    "With the increased use of AI in healthcare, ethical challenges become more apparent.",
    "In 2021 the WHO issued a report on AI in health with six guiding principles for its design and use to address ethical considerations [9].",
    "Managing the permanently increasing volume, variety, and velocity of pharmacovigilance (PV) data in the framework of regulatory requirements presents a remarkable challenge.",
    "One important AI/ML benefit resides in its ability to learn from real-world use and experience, and the AI/ML capability for performance improvement."
